    8 = Object color 0x0A
  end

  stats
    stat at 18,8 element Object p1 cp437:0x6F under Fake color 0x60
    oop
    @Mirel
    :touch
    Mirel does not stand, on principle.
    She has claimed this bench and intends
    to defend it by sitting very hard.
    !key;Ask about the bakery key
    !bread;Ask about the bakery
    #end
    :key
    Oh, the gate key? It fell in the
    fountain. Weeks ago. Nobody wades in
    for a warm roll. Nobody but you, maybe.
    #end
    :bread
    The smell comes right over the wall
    some mornings. It is a kind of cruelty.
    #end
    end
    stat at 20,9 element Object p1 cp437:0x6F under Fake color 0x60
    oop
    @Toben
    :touch
    Toben nods slowly, like a man agreeing
    with the weather.
    !fountain;Ask about the fountain
    !wait;Ask what he is waiting for
    #end
    :fountain
    The key's down in the fountain water.
    East to the plaza, then find the court.
    Wade in. Cold, but that's the price.
    #end
    :wait
    Bread. I am waiting for bread.
    Have been for some time now.
    #end
    end
    stat at 42,16 element Object p1 cp437:0x6F under Fake color 0x60
    oop
    @Old Pell
    :touch
    Old Pell squints at you like you owe
    him an explanation for your youth.
    !advice;Ask for advice
    !bench;Comment on the bench
    #end
    :advice
    Get the key from the fountain, open the
    gate to the north of the plaza, eat
    something baked. That's the whole plot.
    #end
    :bench
    Good bench. Sat here through three
    mayors and one very slow pigeon.
    #end
    end
    stat at 40,8 element Object p1 cp437:0x26 under Fake color 0x60
    oop
    @Pigeon
    :touch
    The pigeon regards you with total,
    unearned confidence.
    #play tc
    #end
    end
  end
end

